definition.value: A  haloamino acid that is an amino acid carrying at least one halogen atom.
Any  substituted aniline carrying at least one chloro group.
Any organochlorine compound containing a benzene ring which is substituted by one or more chlorines.
Alpelisib is a phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase (PI3K) inhibitor with potent antitumor activity.

Tris(4-chlorophenyl)methanol (TCPMOH) is a water contaminant with unknown etiology, but is believed to be a byproduct of DDT manufacturing. It is highly persistent in the environment, and bioaccumulates in marine species.
TCPM is structurally related to the organochlorine pesticide Dichlorodiphenyltrichloroethane (DDT), and evidence suggests they are likely manufacturing byproducts of this legacy contaminant
